  "body": "# Problem\r\nWhen users have assigned a nickname, they likely expect to mention people by their nickname and only ever see the nickname as a way to recognize the given user. However, if users enter a nickname this might lead to collisions; People in the chat might have a ENS name that is the same as the nickname. This problem is addressed by letting people select the mention from a suggestion list.\r\n\r\nDiscussed flow:\r\n- hierarchy Nickname, ENS name, 3-word name is followed in mentions\r\n- when user enters @ mention suggestion list appears\r\n- when user enters @x mention suggestion list appears with relevant users. This can be nickname starting with x or ens name starting with x (collision case) - both will including random name to differentiate\r\n- when user taps on user in mention suggestion list, ENS/3w-name is shown in chat input box, highlighted as mention\r\n- when user hits send, mention is shown in message as nickname\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\n\r\n## Acceptance Criteria\r\nUser can select nickname as mention and view nickname in chat message\r\n\r\n\r\n",
